			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Tired of hearing the paradox of needing career experience to kick-start your career? Well we&rsquo;re looking for the right people to help us in our expanding marketing team, giving successful candidates the chance to gain valuable industry experience at one of the world&rsquo;s leading social media technology companies.<br />
We are growing fast and need someone who can hit the ground running, and work collaboratively with a global team of marketers and community managers.<br />
<br />
You will be based in our New York, NY office, though there might in some cases be the option to spend some of your time working remotely.&nbsp;This will initially be on a three month internship, though there may be the opportunity to later develop this into a full-time position.<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities include</strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
&bull; Coordinate event logistics and provide general support and project management of multiple marketing projects<br />
&bull; Assisting on writing and editing marketing content and reports, from blog posts to longer pieces<br />
&bull; Contributing to and becoming a part of useful discussions and communities online<br />
&bull; Maintaining and growing some of Brandwatch&rsquo;s social profiles<br />
&bull; Contact influential people and companies to generate hype and traffic around Brandwatch&rsquo;s product and activity<br />
&bull; Research top influencers, competitors and trends in the industry</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
&bull; Experience in social media, writing and relevant industries is desired, but not necessary<br />
&bull; Ideal candidates will have a bachelor&rsquo;s degree, preferably in media, marketing or public relations<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal and creative writing skills<br />
&bull; Knowledge and/or experience optimising use of leading social networking tools such as Twitter, Facebook, YouTube, LinkedIn, etc.<br />
&bull; An ability to build social networks and establish meaningful relationships<br />
&bull; Knowledge of social media technology sectors is a plus but not required</p>
<p>
<strong>Why apply to join Brandwatch?</strong><br />
Successful candidates will be working with a young, energetic and rapidly growing company in an exciting, innovative industry. Brandwatch believes strongly in staff development and is looking to hire people who have the potential and desire to build a career with the company. We offer a host of benefits, a fun work experience and opportunities for growth.</p>
